{
  "info": {
    "name": "URL Shortener",
    "description": "Endpoints for the URL shortener (Better Auth + shorten/redirect/analytics).\n\nCollection variables:\n- baseUrl: http://localhost:3000\n- sessionToken: auto-filled from the `set-auth-token` response header on Sign Up / Sign In\n- verificationToken: paste the `token` query param from the verification email link\n- jwtToken: auto-filled by Get JWT Token (optional, for stateless validation)\n- shortCode: auto-filled by Create Short URL\n\nFlow (production): Sign Up -> check email -> Verify Email -> Sign In -> Create Short URL -> ...\nFlow (development): Sign Up -> Sign In -> Create Short URL -> ...\n\nAuth uses Better Auth with the bearer plugin. The session token is returned in the `set-auth-token` header — not in the JSON body. Use `Authorization: Bearer {{sessionToken}}` on protected routes.\n\nEmail verification is built into Better Auth at `GET /api/auth/verify-email?token=...` (no custom route file). In production, sign-in is blocked until verified.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "baseUrl", "value": "http://localhost:3000" },
    { "key": "sessionToken", "value": "" },
    { "key": "verificationToken", "value": "" },
    { "key": "jwtToken", "value": "" },
    { "key": "shortCode", "value": "" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Health",
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [],
        "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/health", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["health"] }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Ready",
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [],
        "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/ready", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["ready"] }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Auth",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Auth OK",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('status ok', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().status).to.eql('ok'));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/ok",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "ok"]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Sign Up (email)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "const token = pm.response.headers.get('set-auth-token');",
                  "if (token) pm.collectionVariables.set('sessionToken', token);",
                  "pm.test('2xx success', () => pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([200, 201]));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"Test User\",\n  \"email\": \"user@example.com\",\n  \"password\": \"password123\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/sign-up/email",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "sign-up", "email"]
            },
            "description": "Creates an account. The session token is in the `set-auth-token` response header (bearer plugin).\n\nIn production, a verification email is sent and sign-in is blocked until verified."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Send Verification Email",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": ["pm.test('2xx success', () => pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([200, 201]));"]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"user@example.com\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/send-verification-email",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "send-verification-email"]
            },
            "description": "Resends the verification email. Use the same email as Sign Up.\n\nIn dev, the link is logged in the server console. In production, check your inbox or the Resend dashboard."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Verify Email",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": ["pm.test('2xx success', () => pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([200, 201, 302]));"]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/verify-email?token={{verificationToken}}",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "verify-email"],
              "query": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{verificationToken}}" }]
            },
            "description": "Better Auth built-in route — not a custom file in src/.\n\n1. Open the verification email from Sign Up (or Send Verification Email).\n2. Copy the `token` query param from the link, e.g.\n   `http://localhost:3000/api/auth/verify-email?token=PASTE_THIS`\n3. Set collection variable `verificationToken` to that value.\n4. Run this request (or just click the link in the email).\n\nThen run Sign In."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Sign In (email)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "const token = pm.response.headers.get('set-auth-token');",
                  "if (token) pm.collectionVariables.set('sessionToken', token);",
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"user@example.com\",\n  \"password\": \"password123\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/sign-in/email",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "sign-in", "email"]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Session",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": ["pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));"]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{sessionToken}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/get-session",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "get-session"]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get JWT Token",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "const res = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (res.token) pm.collectionVariables.set('jwtToken', res.token);",
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{sessionToken}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/token",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "token"]
            },
            "description": "Returns a verifiable EdDSA JWT (jwt plugin). Validate statelessly via JWKS."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "JWKS",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/jwks",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "jwks"]
            },
            "description": "Public keys for verifying JWTs from GET /api/auth/token."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Request Password Reset",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": ["pm.test('2xx success', () => pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([200, 201]));"]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"user@example.com\",\n  \"redirectTo\": \"{{baseUrl}}/reset-password\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/request-password-reset",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "request-password-reset"]
            },
            "description": "Sends a password reset email (logged in dev, sent via Resend in production)."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Sign Out",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": ["pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));"]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{sessionToken}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/sign-out",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "sign-out"]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Revoke All Sessions",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": ["pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));"]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{sessionToken}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/revoke-sessions",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "revoke-sessions"]
            },
            "description": "Signs out everywhere — invalidates all sessions for the user."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "URLs",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Create Short URL",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "const res = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (res.code) pm.collectionVariables.set('shortCode', res.code);",
                  "pm.test('201 Created', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{sessionToken}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"url\": \"https://example.com/some/very/long/path?with=query\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/urls",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "urls"]
            },
            "description": "Optional fields: customAlias (3-32 chars) and expiresAt (future ISO date), e.g.\n{\n  \"url\": \"https://example.com\",\n  \"customAlias\": \"promo\",\n  \"expiresAt\": \"2030-01-01T00:00:00Z\"\n}"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "List My URLs",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{sessionToken}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/urls?limit=20&offset=0",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "urls"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "limit", "value": "20" },
                { "key": "offset", "value": "0" }
              ]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "URL Stats",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{sessionToken}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/urls/{{shortCode}}/stats",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "urls", "{{shortCode}}", "stats"]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Delete Short URL",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": ["pm.test('204 No Content', () => pm.response.to.have.status(204));"]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "DELETE",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{sessionToken}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/urls/{{shortCode}}",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "urls", "{{shortCode}}"]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Redirect (follow short code)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/{{shortCode}}",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["{{shortCode}}"]
            },
            "description": "Returns a 302 to the original URL (410 if expired). Tip: disable Settings > 'Automatically follow redirects' to see the 302 + Location header."
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
